==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Sleight
<hw>Sleight</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OE.
<ets>sleighte</ets>, <ets>sleihte</ets>, <ets>sleithe</ets>, Icel.
<ets>sl<?/g<?/</ets> (for <ets>sl<?/g<?/</ets>) slyness, cunning, fr.
<ets>sl<?/gr</ets> (for <ets>sl<?/gr</ets>) sly, cunning. See
<er>Sly</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Cunning; craft; artful
practice.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark> ⟦ldquo⟧His <xex>sleight</xex> and
his covin.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Chaucer.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>An artful trick; sly artifice; a feat so dexterous
that the manner of performance escapes observation.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The world hath many subtle <qex>sleights</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Latimer.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Dexterous practice; dexterity; skill.</def>
<au>Chaucer.</au> ⟦ldquo⟧The juggler's <xex>sleight</xex>.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Hudibras.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Sleight of hand</b></col>, <cd>legerdemain;
prestidigitation.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><-- p. 1354 --></p>

<p><ent>Sleightful</ent>⟦br⟧
